can always be expressed as a definable formula_41-adic integral. Applying a result of MacIntyre on the model theory of formula_51-adic integers, one deduces again that formula_52 is a rational function in formula_18. Moreover, M. du Sautoy and F. Grunewald showed that the integral can be approximated by Artin L-functions. Using the fact that Artin L-functions are holomorphic in a neighbourhood of the line formula_54, they showed that for any torsionfree nilpotent group, the function formula_48 is meromorphic in the domain

